        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The glycosylated membrane protein M of the severe acute respiratory syndrome associated coronavirus ( SARS - CoV ) is the main structural component of the virion",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "and mediates assembly and budding of viral particles . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The membrane topology of SARS - CoV M and the functional significance of its N - glycosylation are not completely understood",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "as is its interaction with the surface glycoprotein S. <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Using biochemical and immunofluorescence analyses",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "we found",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "that M consists of a short glycosylated N - terminal ectodomain , three transmembrane segments and a long , immunogenic C - terminal endodomain . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Although the N - glycosylation site of M seems to be highly conserved between group 1 and 3 coronaviruses ,",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "studies",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "using a recombinant SARS - CoV",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "expressing a glycosylation - deficient M",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "revealed",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that N - glycosylation of M neither influence the shape of the virions nor their infectivity in cell culture . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "Further functional analysis of truncated M proteins showed",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "that the N - terminal 134 amino acids",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "comprising the three transmembrane domains",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "are sufficient",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "to mediate accumulation of M in the Golgi complex",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 18,
            "text": "and to enforce recruitment of the viral spike protein S to the sites of virus assembly and budding in the ERGIC . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        }
    ]
}